This paper deals with the containment problem for Conditional Tree Patterns (CTP), which are used in XML data processing. This topic is closely related to database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of temporal logic, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the expressive power of CTP and its relationship to Regular XPath and first-order logic, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
